INTRODUCTION

  Stephane is a tiny shim that makes it trivially easy to serve Django apps with 
  Aspen. Aspen is a Python webserver, a good fit for pure-HTTP Django deployment.

    http://code.google.com/p/aspen-commons/wiki/Stephane
    http://www.zetadev.com/software/aspen/
 

QUICK START

  1. Create a new Django project <foo> next to __.
  2. Edit __/etc/aspen.conf, and set settings_module to <foo>.settings.
  3. Start aspen in the parent of __.
